RACE.RACE_TEXT: TURFWAY PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 85. Maiden Special Weight Purse 70000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $30,000).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIBERTANGO Saved ground setting the early pace, drifted out slightly entering the stretch while opening clear and maintained a safe advantage. ISOCLINE was prominent from the start while racing along the inside and finished well for the place in a steady effort. FAST FORWARD saved ground while being unhurried, slipped though along the inside on the turn and was gaining slightly late. RUNANDSCORE was allowed to settle in stride while racing two-wide on the turn, came three-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. REGAL REY hopped in the air at the start, then racing five-wide on the turn, came six-wide into the stretch and finished willingly. METATRON'S MUSE was forwardly placed for a half mile while racing three-wide and gave way. NOW THAT ICAN ROCK dropped back early while racing two-wide and failed to threaten. OBSERVE was prominent to the stretch while racing four-wide and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Libertango
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, drifted out, held advantage

ENTRY.NAME: Observe
ENTRY.OWNER: Claiborne Farm and Dilschneider, Adele B.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TURFWAY PARK RACE 2 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 19000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEATLOAF'S CHANCE was reserved off the early pace, launched a four-wide bid on the turn, took the lead entering the stretch, drifted in during the drive and drew clear late. KICK ROCKS KID broke out to brush with One Ace, then saved ground setting the pressured pace, responded when headed, steadied while in tight nearing the eighth pole and continued on gamely to the wire when clear. THE BOATMAN prompted the pace while racing two-wide, was unable to stay with the top two late but continued on well for the show. SAMURAI ISLAND was prominently placed while racing three-wide but lacked a rally when called upon. SCOTCH NO ROCKS was forwardly placed from between horses and went evenly. FLOYD G broke in to bump with One Ace at the start, then saved ground and failed to threaten. LONGER VIEW was unhurried early, came four-wide into the stretch and was not a factor. ONE ACE was pinched back at the start, then dropped well back and failed to menace. ILLUSIONED showed early speed from between horses, steadied leaving the half mile pole in tight and gave way. The Jockey of KICK ROCKS KID lodged an objection against MEATLOAF"S CHANCE, but after viewing the films, the stewards made no change in the order of finish.

ENTRY.NAME: Kick Rocks Kid
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, set pressure pace, responded, steadied 1/8, gamely

ENTRY.COMMENT: pinched start, dropped back, no menace

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HURRY HURRY was reserved off the early pace, moved up strongly three-wide leaving the quarter pole, took the lead entering the stretch and drew clear late. CAESAR'S GHOST saved ground tracking the pace, slipped through to offer a bid nearing the eighth pole but was unable to match strides with the winner late. RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUTADORE dueled for the lead from the outset while racing four-wide, opened clear nearing the eighth pole and maintained a safe advantage. BAKERS BAY was unhurried early, rallied six-wide into the stretch and finished fast. DIVINE LEADER prompted the issue while racing two-wide and held on well for the show. JOHNNY UNLEASHED dropped back early and was not a factor. PETIT VERDOT raced between horses on the turn, bobbled nearing the three-eighths pole unseating his rider and was vanned off. The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the incident involving PETIE VERDOT, but after viewing the films, made no change in the order of finish.
